Package: FastImputation
Type: Package
Title: Learn from Training Data then Quickly Fill in Missing Data
Version: 3.0.0
Date: 2026-03-22
Authors@R: person(given = c("Stephen", "R."),
                  family = "Haptonstahl",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "srh@haptonstahl.org")
Description: Uses training data to learn a multivariate normal distribution
    that the variables approximate (or can be transformed to approximate),
    storing the result as a 'fast_imputation_patterns' object. Missing values
    are then imputed row-by-row using the conditional multivariate normal
    formula. Column selection follows 'tidyselect' conventions and the package
    integrates with 'recipes' via step_fast_imputation(). The approach
    approximates the method used by 'Amelia' but is optimised for fast
    single-row imputation.
